BUSINESSDESC: Sol Systems is leading the way to streamline financing for the solar industry, making the investment process more efficient and less costly for homeowners, installers, and investors. Sol Systems aggregates diverse capital sources to provide a synthetic financing source for developers of commercial solar projects in the U.S. and Canada. The company first entered the market providing the first long-term contracts for solar renewable energy credits (SRECs), a commodity-based incentive that is essential for financing solar on the East Coast. Before Sol Systems was founded, SREC markets were reserved for large, utility-scale projects. It was difficult for homeowners and small businesses to monetize SRECs because of the transaction costs associated with smaller systems. Sol Systems revolutionized SREC markets by aggregating SRECs from thousands of small system owners and then selling them into contracts with energy suppliers, who needed to purchase them to meet state law. In 2011, Sol Systems began focusing on commercial solar, the sector of the solar market with the lowest historical growth due to high transaction costs and a lack of capital. Today, Sol Systems has evolved to offer solar developers access a full suite of solar financing products, including construction and term debt, sponsor and tax equity, full purchase financing, and SREC solutions. Sol Systems also provides developer partners with market information and guidance on best practices to increase the likelihood that a project will receive financing. One of the biggest issues in the industry is fragmented investment channels that create friction in the market. By pooling these together, Sol Systems serves as a conduit of capital and investment opportunities for the industrys investors and developers. The firm has facilitated financing for over 90 MW of solar energy, enough to provide clean, green electricity to approximately 10,500 homes, promoting U.S. energy independence and increasing solar deployment.
CATEGORIES: Local Business Enterprise (LBE);Small Business Enterprise (SBE);Resident Owned Business (ROB);

BUSINESSDESC: Opportunity Knocks, Inc., a small, woman-owned company, was established in 1997 as a DC corporation. We provide organization development (OD)/change, human resources (HR), communications, training, facilitation, information technology (IT) planning, and conference consulting services across government, non-profit, & private organizations. The company also has a youth leadership/teambuilding program used by private schools & parent groups. The company was founded on the belief that change leads to opportunity. Our clients are facing constant change but are still accountable for: setting direction, attaining goals, executing plans, and making decisions. We help our clients effectively manage near term tasks while facilitating strategy development regarding future opportunities. The focus of our practice is serving clients who are planning for: (1) growth or transformation, (2) realignment of HR practices to connect with business strategy, and (3) preparation for deployment & implementation of information technologies (e.g., software, telecommunications, etc.) impacting their way of doing business. Simultaneously, we work to improve their interpersonal, team, leadership, or overall organization performance by providing OD solutions such as teambuilding, leadership development, and/or training. We also create communications strategies connected to the changes that are occurring and recommend/work to implement innovative HR solutions. Specifically, we design improvements to HR performance management systems and design reorganizations. Our staff has diverse skills (and most with advance degrees) in OD, HR, facilitation, conference planning, communications/marketing, and IT project management. Although we have served dozens of clients since incorporating, 2014 clients include: U.S. Internal Revenue Service, U.S.D.A. Forest Service, CGI Federal, Constellation West, National Public Radio, Space Exploration Technologies, and Healthy Companies International/MedStar Health.

BUSINESSDESC: MSC will offer residents, employees and visitors to the St. Elizabeths campus a new concept—food choices that are minimally-processed. For example, breakfast options feature grass-fed meats and cage free eggs (e.g., whole grain pancakes, French toast, fresh seasonal fruits, whole grain hot cereals, breads, muffins and pastries). During lunch, the fare will include fresh soups, house-made burgers, signature sandwiches, smoothies, garden fresh seasonal salads with homemade and nutritious dressings, signature pies, cakes and cookies, and locally inspired beverages. Only three of the more than 30 farmers markets in the District of Columbia are located east of the Anacostia River. NSL has entered into an agreement with DMPED to provide 10 hours of programming each month at Gateway DC and/or the R.I.S.E. Demonstration Center. The programs (nutrition counseling, basic food handling, cooking classes, and interactive food demonstrations) will be offered in a state-of-the-art teaching kitchen at low or no-cost to the public. To support this effort, NSL will utilize Ms. Bailey-Joyners previous experience as well as a consultant with considerable expertise in developing successful community mapping and outreach programs focused on improving access to healthy food options. More than 6,000 employees at the St. Elizabeths campus will purchase fresh snacks and meals from MSC, the only full-service restaurant in the St. Elizabeths East Gateway Pavilion. This inviting and historic183-acre campus setting will also serve as a gathering place that provides information, free Wi-Fi services, offer guests a library with more than 1,000 books and during the evening hours cooking demonstrations to help individuals make incremental but critical changes to their diet and food choices. The opening of MSC on the St. Elizabeths campus also improves commercial vibrancy along one of the Districts emerging corridors and in surrounding neighborhoods.

BUSINESSDESC: Sustainable Facilities Management Services (SFMS) is a small economically disadvantaged woman-owned minority business located in Washington, DC. It was founded in 2013 to provide sustainable facilities management services and solutions to Federal and local governments, commercial and industrial markets utilizing the “Green Building” methodology. Our leadership team, collectively, has over 50 years of experience consolidated facilities management services and strategic planning and execution in the federal, state, local governments and commercial and industrial markets. We offer our clients cost effective, high quality, sustainable facilities and operations maintenance and management. Our Green Building methodology utilize policies, procedures, processes and standards to increase the efficiencies with which resources, energy, water and materials are used; while reducing building impacts on human health and the environment through superior operations and maintenance programs. We accomplish this utilizing a “fully integrated, holistic approach to operations and maintenance for all of our project sites”. We believe that our customers want and desire services that are both, cost effective and sustainable over time. SFMS is not your typical conventional linear facilities management company where operations and maintenance services and processes are independently managed. Instead we offer our clients sustainable building operations using the green building methodology. Our sustainability methods and practices rely on our fully integrated holistic approach, using the LEED for Existing Buildings Operation and Maintenance Rating System (EBO&M) as a framework for maintenance operation and improvements, and documenting sustainable..

BUSINESSDESC: RCM of Washington, Inc. is a social service provider in the District since 1998. RCM assists adults with intellectual and developmental disabilities (IDD) improve their quality of life through residential, day and employment services. RCM can also serve as an Administrative Services Organization or Fiscal Intermediary. Partnered with the Department on Disability Services (DDS) and other District agencies, the scope of residential services includes housing, daily living, social skill development, medical care coordination, and transportation services. RCM provides customized and individualized in-home supports to assist people develop daily living skills, supports families through respite services, and provides guidance and monitoring for host homes. RCM is a person-centered organization and focuses on providing customized supports based on input of those served to promote growth and independence to maximize goal achievement and desired outcomes. RCM community-based day program focuses on ‘neighborhood networking and assists with creating natural supports and ongoing relationships with neighbors and community partners. All of our programs, including employment readiness, day habilitation and individualized day supports meet the criteria of the new definition of community services by Centers of Medicare and Medicaid (CMS). RCMs employment team provides a variety of services through both RSA and DDS funding sources; including intake & assessment, job development and placement, job coaching and follow along supports. Our team has an excellent track record of identifying the strengths of job seekers and customizing their employment search. RCM is a leading provider of customized employment and discovery techniques and provides training and consultation to other organizations in the DMV area. We can also provide training in an array of other IDD services and supports.

BUSINESSDESC: KGO proactively manages your renovation, relocation or new building project. We become an integral part of the project process performing overall planning, creating schedules, creating and maintaining project budgets, procuring competitive and best prices, ensuring quality, and anticipating and resolving issues. KGO approaches each project as if it were our own. We become an extension to your staff bringing an expertise to your side. During a project, hundreds of decisions must be made. While we dont make the decisions for you, we identify the issues and perform all the analysis necessary for you to make a timely and informed decision. Our objective is to create well-run and successful projects—projects that complete on-time, within budget and reflect high quality. We develop a project budget for all project costs including professional design services, building permits, construction, voice and data cabling, telephone equipment, moving, and furniture along with appropriate project contingencies. Throughout the project, we update the budget as the costs become refined. Because of our extensive experience, we know which contractors and vendors are best suited for your project and who are offering the best price. We also know the customary cost for the various budget items, and we ensure that the charges to our clients are appropriate. Our team-oriented approach creates smooth running projects where the team members—the architects and designers, contractors and vendors—are proud to be involved. Of course every project has its issues to resolve and disagreements to negotiate, but when handled in a professional, fair, and consistent way, conflicts and frustrations are prevented or avoided.

BUSINESSDESC: Development Institute llc has the following core business lines: 1) Organisational and Program Effectiveness There is a growing emphasis on measuring program effectiveness in the international operational environment. Organizations that are able to show results can deliver better and more cost-efficient services and be more marketable to funders looking for outcome achievement rather than quantity of efforts. Navigating this increasingly results-oriented environment requires focus on monitoring and evaluation (M&E) and dedication to using results for program improvement. Organisations making decisions based on data and analytics hold a sustainable competitive advantage over others; they have a better understanding of the current program conditions and the ability to plan for future service improvement to increase the impact of the Organisation. We believe that effective programs rely on three core pillars: people, process and structure. Organisations need talented people with the skill-sets to excel at their jobs, processes that increase efficiencies and a structure that encourages data-backed decision-making. 2) Social and Environmental Impact; Before undertaking large projects, an organisation must first ensure that requirements have been met to satisfy local and national regulations. This often involves a social impact assessment as well as a consultation with the public that may be affected by the project. Here at Institute for Development Impact we begin our approach with a thorough examination of the proposed project and its impact both socially and environmentally. We are a new age international development company that combines intellectual leadership of a think-tank institution with an on the ground practice-oriented technical application of solutions that work.

BUSINESSDESC: The mission of Life Enhancement Services (LES) is “To support and encourage personal growth and independence in the developmentally, socially, and mentally challenged individuals we serve by providing options and adhering to their choices.” Life Enhancement Services of DC is a provider of quality bi-lingual services to clients with mental disorders, behavioral disorders, and with alcohol and drug addiction. LES clients benefit from a Person-Centered treatment approach. The philosophy is to work tirelessly with clients to help them achieve their desired outcomes and triumph over the issues that brought them to us. The goal of community-based programs in this model is to carefully work with naturally occurring units of solution as our units of practice, or where and how we choose to intervene. This necessitates a careful assessment of community structures and processes, in advance, of any intervention. It also requires an insiders understanding of the community to identify and work with these naturally occurring units of solution to address community problems. Thus, the aim is to strengthen these units of solution to better meet the needs of community members. This approach may include strengthening community through neighborhood organizations and network linkages, including informal social networks, ties between individuals and the organizations that serve them, and connections among community organizations to strengthen their ability to collaborate. The model also necessitates addressing issues of common concern for the community, many or most of which are not directly health issues. In other words, this model necessitates starting where people are.

Additional financing programs and vehicles of interest include TIFIA, RRIF, Private Activity Bonds (PAB), and INFRA Grants. TerraSom possesses a unique combination of technical, operational, and financial expertise in these areas, at the local, state, and national level. We have developed a significant network of relationships and infrastructure industry knowledge, enabling us to provide objective and independent advice to our clients and their senior management. Arpan Patel, PMP, the owner and President of TerraSom, has developed a unique combination of qualifications, experience, and relationships over the last 25 years to provide advice and guidance to the various constituencies involved in the financing, building, and operating of public infrastructure. These relationships include financial institutions, institutional investors, and private investors from his tenure as a Wall Street financier and founder of an investment software startup. They also include federal, state, and local government agencies, and infrastructure industry service providers, such as leading architecture and engineering firms, construction companies, and operators, developed as a project manager at an award-winning infrastructure consulting firm and as a real estate developer. BUSINESSDESC: InSite Solutions is a school-based mental health consulting and service organization founded and operated by child psychologists that specializes in the implementation, enhancement, and delivery of school-based mental health services for children ages pre-k through grade 12. InSite Solutions model has core four components: A detailed needs assessment allows InSite Solutions team to assess the rates, types, and frequency of psychopathology, psychosocial stressors, and special educational needs within each school we serve. Next, we assess existing mental health systems and policies, and, where needed, recommend enhancements, including InSite Solutions mobile data tracking tools; to most effectively support the social/emotional needs of students. We also provide ongoing training for school personnel in evidence-based practices including evidenced-based behavioral health curricula within the classroom, school-wide frameworks for positive behavioral supports, fundamentals in classroom behavior management, support in implementation of social-emotional curricula, and training in evidence-based interventions. Central to InSite Solutions mission is an emphasis to mitigate barriers to high quality empirically validated mental health care for school-aged children across Washington, DC. Thus, via InSite Solutions Clinic Without Walls model, students can benefit from the most effective forms of mental health support available in our region, all within the convenience of their school and at no charge to the childs family. These services include: Individualized evidenced-based psychotherapy from doctoral level psychologist, parent resource centers to help support improved family functioning, access to board certified child psychiatrists to write and manage medications as needed, case consultation to school staff for children with high mental health needs, and access to our community referral and liaison services network.

BUSINESSDESC:
OVERVIEW
C&S Materials is a wholesale distributor of pipe, valve, and fittings. Our product offering is primarily waterworks & site utilities & as such our current source for said product is via wholesale distributor James M. Cox Company, Inc. We then work with our customer base on per project basis from initial design & takeoffs to the satisfactory delivery of materials required. We work on a “Just in Time” inventory practice. We utilize and work closely with our manufacturers and their production facilities & warehouses. The majority of our manufacturers have facilities within 2-3 days ship times on all materials. As such we work with our customer in planning accordingly to facilitate their needs.

The materials used in the waterworks & site utilities industries arent products that are readily available
online. It would be almost impossible to do so. We are talking about pipe & fittings in excess of 60”
diameter at times. We pride ourselves in performing accurate takeoffs from engineering drawings and
procuring those items as efficiently possible.

OUR PROCESS
• We receive orders through our 8-step process:
• Initial Inquiry: Meet with customer to go over their needs.
• Quote: Furnish customer quote based on takeoff/conversation (sample included with this packet)
• Follow up: We determine if there are any other products our customer requires.
• Customer PO: Customer issues us PO for material.
• Order Confirmation: Confirm receipt of PO with customer and assure accuracy.
• Purchase Order: Place PO to wholesaler for material.
• Delivery: Work with manufacturer on logistics of entire shipping process, (ie. source, terms, etc.).
• Invoice: Invoice customer upon satisfactory delivery of materials. We have net 30 terms with our
contractor clients, but entities such as the DLA, Water Authorities, etc. dictate terms. Most
payments are accepted via ACH, check or credit card.
CATEGORIES: Local Business Enterprise (LBE);Disadvantaged Business Enterprise (DBE);Small Business Enterprise (SBE);Development Enterprise Zone (DZE);Resident Owned Business (ROB);

BUSINESSDESC: CTI District Services, Inc. is a District-based business that provides Third-Party Code Compliance Inspections and Whole Building Commissioning Services. CTI District Services provides Third Party Code Compliance Inspections which is a program utilized by DCRA and other governmental organizations to promote economic development. CTI District Services will be a third party organizations that employs personnel who meet the requirements set forth by DCRA for providing these services within their jurisdiction. Once CTI District Services completes the Third Party Inspections Program Application process with DCRA, they will be allowed to contract directly with permit applicants to provide inspection services on behalf of the public agency. CTI District Services employs an inspection staff certified by the International Code Council and include multi-disciplined Combination Inspectors and Certified Building Offices. Having a multi-disciplined inspector ensures consistent inspections by the same inspector for all trades. Multi-disciplined inspectors also provide the construction teams with a single point of contact throughout the duration of the project. We assist our clients in overcoming one of the most difficult challenges facing our governmental clients: being responsive to the communities they serve in an environment that requires an attitude of facilitation and quick decision-making. CTI District Services also provides Whole Building Commissioning (Cx) Services for new construction and retro commissioning services for owners of government, commercial, and private buildings. Our Certified Professional performs Fundamental and Enhanced Commissioning of Heating, Ventilating, Air-Conditioning, and Refrigerating (HVAC&R) and Building Enclosures (BECx). BUSINESSDESC: CHL Business Interiors, Inc. (“CHL”) is a full-line, full-service contract office furniture and related services provider. CHLs primary market is the Washington, DC metropolitan area. However, because of the national and international make up of many of its clients, it is often called upon to manage projects in many parts of the country. Most recently, CHL has completed projects in California, Boston, Oregon, and New York. Internationally, CHL has completed projects in China, France, Australia, and Great Britain. CHLs staff has been engaged exclusively in the dealer segment with experience ranging from 5 to 25 years. CHL knows the market, knows the industry, and has a loyal client following to attest to its capabilities. CHL positions itself as an independent, multiple line dealer offering a broad range of product and service solutions for both the commercial and GSA markets. CHL is not driven by imposed quotas, but rather by its clients needs that are often best served from a wider variety of possible solutions. CHL also positions itself as a facility management service, offering a comprehensive assortment of services consistent with the increasing needs of its clients. CHL prides itself on having the most complete Project Management department in the Washington, DC metropolitan area. Upon award of a project, CHL will meet with all of the involved parties to determine the exact requirements of the project and tailor its management approach to meet the needs of the project. All of the members of the CHL project team-along with the installation personnel-are factory-trained, certified, and authorized for all of the furniture they are proposing. Additionally, the members of the CHL project team have many years of experience and are well versed in the concerns and problems that may arise during an installation and know how to deal with them. CHL also provides extensive design services.
